        "created_at": "2020-05-09T08:58:29.087Z",
        "cooked": "<p>When using multiple backup_agent with local url on different nodes, backup file may be distributed in different nodes (same path).</p>\n<p>So, does combining the backup files of all the nodes together make a complete backup?</p>\n<p>Then, does this complete backup need to be copied to each node at the time of recovery?<br>\n(maybe only one full backup is needed, other nodes are part of the file at the time of backup?)</p>\n<p>Is there any way to use these backup files for recovery in a distributed manner?<br>\n(do not put them together, and copy to each node)</p>",
