        "created_at": "2020-05-09T09:13:07.280Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The idea is that backups should either go to an S3 style blob service or to a remote file system (such as NFS) that is locally mounted at the same path on each host running a backup_agent so you can use a local path such as <code>file:///mount/some_filesystem/backup123</code> to read and write it.</p>\n<p>If you do choose to write to a path which is local-only on each host, then yes if you combine all of the files together into the same folder (preserving their paths within the backup folder) then you will have a complete backup and every <code>backup_agent</code> will need access to this folder during a restore.</p>",
